5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 500, L.D. 1211, “An Act Regarding
10 Certain Definitions in the Sales and Use Tax Laws Affecting Rental Equipment and
11 Automobiles Used in Transporting Goods”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act Regarding Certain Definitions in the Sales and Use Tax Laws Affecting
14 Rental Equipment'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §1752, sub-§5-D, ¶E is enacted to read:
18 E. Grants of a privilege to use sports or recreational equipment for a period not
19 exceeding 7 continuous days when the value of the use of that sports or recreational
20 equipment is less than $100 per day and the use of the sports or recreational equipment
21 is restricted to use on the premises of the grantor of the privilege to use the sports or
22 recreational equipment.
23 As used in this paragraph:
24 (1) "Premises" means a building or specific area owned or leased by the grantor
25 of the privilege or to which the grantor has an exclusive right or use of the space at
26 which sports or recreational equipment that the grantor allows other persons to use
27 is kept; and
28 (2) "Sports or recreational equipment" means items designed for human use used
29 in conjunction with an athletic or similar recreational activity that are not suitable
30 for general use.'
31 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
32 number to read consecutively.
